TextEquiv.Unicode: But children of the heav'nly King ,
But children of the heav'nly King ,
Let those refuse to sing Who never knew our God ; But children of the heav'nly King , But children of the heav'nly King ,
THE PRIZE IS SET BEFORE US .
THE PRIZE IS SET BEFORE US .
The prize is set before us-
To win , our Lord implores us !
The eye of God is o'er us ,
From on high , from on high !
He is nigh , He is nigh .

The prize is set before us- To win , our Lord implores us ! The eye of God is o'er us , From on high , from on high ! His loving tones are falling , While sin is dark , appaling ; ' Tis Jesus gently calling- He is nigh , He is nigh .
CHO . - By and by we shall meet Him ,
By and by we shall greet Him ,
And with Jesus reign in glory ,
By and by , by and by ;
CHO . - By and by we shall meet Him , By and by we shall greet Him , And with Jesus reign in glory , By and by , by and by ;
By and by we shall meet Him ,
By and by we shall greet Him ,
And with Jesus reign in glory ,
By and by we shall meet Him , By and by we shall greet Him , And with Jesus reign in glory , By and by .
We yield to Him who pleadeth
From on high , from on high !
For naught from Him can sever ;
And faith shall fail us never-
He is nigh , He is nigh .

We follow where He leadeth- We pasture where He feedeth- We yield to Him who pleadeth From on high , from on high ! For naught from Him can sever ; Our hope shall brighten ever ; And faith shall fail us never- He is nigh , He is nigh .
Our home is bright above us ;
No trials there to move us ,
But Christ our Lord to love us ,
Dwells on high : dwells on high !
Nearer , my God , to Thee , Nearer to Thee !
E'en though it be a cross
E'en though it be a cross That raiseth me ,
Still all my song shall be ,
Still all my song shall be , Nearer , my God , to Thee , Nearer to Thee !
Though like a wanderer , The sun gone down , Darkness comes over me , My rest a stone ;
Yet in my dreams I'd be
Yet in my dreams I'd be Nearer , my God , to Thee , Nearer to Thee .
In merey given ; Angels to beckon me Nearer , my God , to Thee , Nearer to Thee !
Or , if on joyful wing , Cleaving the sky ,
Sun , moon , and stars forgot , Upward I fly ,
Still all my song shall be ,
Still all my song shall be , Nearer , my God , to Thee , Nearer to Thee .
Come we that love the Lord ,
Come we that love the Lord ,
And let our joys be known ,
Join in a song with sweet accord ,
Join in a song with sweet accord ,
And let our joys be known , Join in a song with sweet accord , Join in a song with sweet accord , And thus surround the throne . And thus surround the throne .
CHO . - We're marching to Zion , Beautiful , beautiful , Zion ; We're marching upward to Zion , The beautiful city of God .
May speak their joys abroad , May speak their joys abroad .
Before we reach the heaven'ly fields ,
Before we reach the heaven'ly fields ,
A thousand sacred sweets , Before we reach the heaven'ly fields , Before we reach the heaven'ly fields , Or walk the golden streets , Or walk the golden streets .
We're marching through Immanuel's ground , We're marching through Immanuel's ground , To fairer worlds on high . To fairer worlds on high .
There's a Stranger at the door ;
There's a Stranger at the door ; Let Him in !
He has been there oft before ;
He has been there oft before ; Let Him in !
Let Him in ere He is gone ;
Let Him in , The Holy One ,
Open now to Him your heart ;
Open now to Him your heart ; Let Him in !
If you wait He will depart ;
If you wait He will depart ; Let Him in !
Let Him in ; He is your Friend ;
And your soul He will defend ,
He will keep you to the end ;
Hear you now His loving voice ;
Hear you now His loving voice ; Let Him in !
Now , oh now , make Him your choice ;
Now , oh now , make Him your choice ; Let Him in !
He is standing at the door ,
He is standing at the door ,
Joy to you He will restore ,
Joy to you He will restore ,
And His name you will adore ;
And His name you will adore ; Let Him in !
Now admit the heav'nly Guest ; Let Him in !
He will make for you a feast ;
He will make for you a feast ; Let Him in !
He will speak your sins forgin'n ,
And when earth - ties all are riv'n ,
He will take you home to heav'n .
He will speak your sins forgin'n , And when earth - ties all are riv'n , He will take you home to heav'n . Let Him in !
All hail the power of Jesus ' name !
And crown Him Lord of all .
And crown Him Lord of all .
Ye chosen seed of Israel's race ,
Hail Him who saves you by His grace ,
And crown Him Lord of all .
Ye chosen seed of Israel's race , Ye ransomed from the fall , Hail Him who saves you by His grace , And crown Him Lord of all .
Sinners , whose love can ne'er forget
Go , spread your trophies at His feet ,
And crown Him Lord of all .
Sinners , whose love can ne'er forget The wormwood and the gall , Go , spread your trophies at His feet , And crown Him Lord of all .
Let every kindred , every tribe , On this terrestrial ball ,
And crown Him Lord of all .
To Him all majesty ascribe , And crown Him Lord of all .
